com/2013/05/08/introducing-vaultpress-lite/\">VaultPress Lite plan announced this morning</a>.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 08 May 2013 18:17:13 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Joseph Scott\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:21;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"WPTavern: How To Search For 100% GPL Themes On Themeforest\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://www.wptavern.com/?p=6831\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:109:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/iD6061j0jLA/how-to-search-for-100-gpl-themes-on-themeforest\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2267:\"<p>Not long ago, <a href=\"http://notes.envato.com/general/100-gpl-option-now-available-plus-woothemes-arrives/\">Themeforest announced</a> that theme authors would be able to choose a 100% GPL theme license. However, as a customer, it&#8217;s difficult to find where those 100% GPL licensed themes are located on the site. Upon browsing the Themeforest Marketplace, I could not find a <em>category, tag, or link</em> that would show me all the WordPress themes licensed as such. Since the text located within the license information box is able to be crawled by Google, you can use a Site specific search query to find these themes. Just type <em>site:http://themeforest.net/item This item is licensed 100% GPL.</em> into Google to see a list of themes that have been indexed. </p>\n<p><a href=\"http://i1.wp.com/www.wptavern.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/themeforestGPL.jpg\" rel=\"thumbnail\"><img src=\"http://i1.wp.com/www.wptavern.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/themeforestGPL.jpg?resize=532%2C265\" alt=\"ThemeForest GPL Search String\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-6838\" /></a></p>\n<p>While I saw 53,800 results listed, not all the results take you directly to the theme page. For example, the License text is also shown on the <a href=\"http://themeforest.net/item/hustle/discussion/4137914\">discussion pages</a> for each theme which is also indexed. Until Themeforest creates a better way of browsing these specific themes, this will have to do. </p>\n<p><strong>Hat Tip:</strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/bradleypotter/statuses/331854378078203904\">@Bradleypotter</a></p>\n<div class=\"yarpp-related-rss\">\n<p>Related posts:<ol>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.wptavern.com/another-company-goes-100-gpl\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Another Company Goes 100% GPL\">Another Company Goes 100% GPL</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.wptavern.com/premiumthemes-net-goes-gpl\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"PremiumThemes.net Goes GPL\">PremiumThemes.net Goes GPL</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.wptavern.com/how-do-i-contribute-to-commercial-gpl-themes\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"How Do I Contribute To Commercial GPL Themes?\">How Do I Contribute To Commercial GPL Themes?</a></li>\n</ol></p>\n</div>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~4/iD6061j0jLA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" />\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5: